LOADMANAGE. The pay to loadsmen;
that is, persons who sail or row before ships,
in barks or small vessels, with instruments
for towing the ship and directing her course,
in order that she may escape the dangers in


-her way. Poth. Des Avaries, no. 137.

LUCRE. Gain in money or goods; profit;
usually in an ill sense, or with the sense of
something base or unworthy. Webster.

LUMINA. Lat. In the civil law. Lights;
windows; openings to obtain light for one’s
building.
